{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775903862698,"sessionID":"ses_283e23117ffebIn2lnNGhmciyb","part":{"id":"prt_d7c1e6f8100113wsFELwiwRlXg","messageID":"msg_d7c1e48e3001j3STxEUIhHqQom","sessionID":"ses_283e23117ffebIn2lnNGhmciyb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d010bd5cc8da444ba50c7979e25b1f61","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement a time-based garbage collection mechanism for Sandbox resources in the Workload Manager. This ensures automatic cleanup of expired and idle sandboxes, preventing resource accumulation and cluster bloat. The GC mechanism provides:\n6: \n7: 1. **TTL Enforcement**: Automatically deletes sandboxes that exceed their `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n8: 2. **Idle Timeout Cleanup**: Removes sandboxes with no activity beyond the configured idle timeout\n9: 3. **Batch Processing**: Limits cleanup operations per cycle to avoid overwhelming the cluster\n10: 4. **Configurable Intervals**: Adjustable GC cycle and idle timeout durations\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector struct with Start/Stop lifecycle, runLoop, runOnce methods |\n19: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior (expired, inactive, batch limits, concurrency) |\n20: | `Store interface extensions` | `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` and `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` methods |\n21: | `GarbageCollectorStats` | Runtime statistics retrieval (Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout) |\n22: | `SetIdleTimeout` | Dynamic idle timeout configuration at runtime |\n23: \n24: ### Key Components\n25: \n26: ```\n27: GarbageCollector\n28: ├── Configuration\n29: │   ├── interval (time.Duration, default: 2m)\n30: │   ├── onceTimeout (time.Duration, default: 2m)\n31: │   └── idleTimeout (time.Duration, default: 15m)\n32: ├── Lifecycle\n33: │   ├── Start() - launches background runLoop goroutine\n34: │   ├── Stop() - graceful shutdown via stopCh\n35: │   └── runLoop() - ticker-driven periodic execution\n36: ├── Cleanup Logic\n37: │   ├── runOnce(ctx) - single GC cycle\n38: │   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes - query expired by ExpiresAt\n39: │   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes - query idle by LastActivity\n40: │   └── Batch deletion (limit: GCBatchSize=16)\n41: └── Runtime Config\n42: │   ├── SetIdleTimeout(timeout)\n43: │   └── GetStats() → GarbageCollectorStats\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ### Out of Scope\n47: \n48: - Kubernetes CronJob-based GC (alternative approach, not selected)\n49: - Webhook-triggered cleanup\n50: - Manual deletion APIs (covered by AR-xxx handlers)\n51: - GC metrics/ Prometheus export (future enhancement)\n52: - Distributed GC coordination across multiple workload-manager instances\n53: \n54: ## Impact Analysis\n55: \n56: ### Upstream Dependencies\n57: \n58: | Dependency | Impact |\n59: |------------|--------|\n60: | `SandboxLifecycleManager` | GC delegates deletion via `DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` |\n61: | `Store` interface | Requires `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` implementations |\n62: | `MemoryStore` | In-memory implementation with expiration/activity indexes |\n63: | `time.Ticker` | Standard library ticker for periodic execution |\n64: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | DeleteOptions for K8s resource cleanup |\n65: \n66: ### Downstream Consumers\n67: \n68: | Consumer | Usage |\n69: |----------|-------|\n70: | `HTTPServer` | Creates and manages GC lifecycle in `NewHTTPServerWithClients` |\n71: | `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox` | GC invokes this for each cleanup target |\n72: | `MemoryStore` | Provides sandbox listing for expired/inactive queries |\n73: | `Integration tests` | Verify GC behavior under concurrent load |\n74: \n75: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n76: \n77: - **Store Interface Extension**: Adding `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` to Store interface requires all implementations to provide these methods\n78: - **Default Idle Timeout**: Changing `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` affects existing sandboxes without explicit timeout annotation\n79: - **GC Interval**: Modifying `GarbageCollectorInterval` impacts cleanup frequency and cluster load\n80: \n81: ## Alternatives Considered\n82: \n83: ### Alternative 1: Kubernetes CronJob-based GC\n84: \n85: **Approach**: Deploy a CronJob that runs periodically to scan and delete expired sandboxes.\n86: \n87: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n88: |--------|------------|\n89: | Pros | Native Kubernetes scheduling; decoupled from workload-manager; easier horizontal scaling |\n90: | Cons | Additional RBAC permissions; delayed cleanup (cron schedule granularity); no idle timeout support; requires separate deployment |\n91: \n92: **Decision**: Rejected. In-process GC provides immediate cleanup after TTL expiry, tighter integration with lifecycle management, and idle timeout handling that CronJob cannot efficiently implement.\n93: \n94: ### Alternative 2: Event-driven Cleanup (Webhook)\n95: \n96: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes admission webhook or event handler to trigger cleanup on resource changes.\n97: \n98: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n99: |--------|------------|\n100: | Pros | Real-time cleanup; no periodic scanning overhead |\n101: | Cons | Complex webhook setup; requires watch on all Sandbox resources; cannot handle idle timeout without additional state |\n102: \n103: **Decision**: Rejected. Timer-based GC is simpler, covers both TTL and idle timeout cases, and matches the workload-manager's controller-like architecture.\n104: \n105: ### Alternative 3: TTL Controller Delegation\n106: \n107: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes TTL controller (built-in for Jobs/Pods) or custom controller for cleanup.\n108: \n109: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n110: |--------|------------|\n111: | Pros | Native controller pattern; standard K8s mechanisms |\n112: | Cons | TTL controller doesn't support custom resources; idle timeout not part of TTL spec |\n113: \n114: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter are custom CRDs; built-in TTL controller doesn't support them. Custom TTL annotation handling requires in-process logic.\n115: \n116: ### Alternative 4: Distributed GC with Leader Election\n117: \n118: **Approach**: Multiple workload-manager instances coordinate cleanup via leader election.\n119: \n120: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n121: |--------|------------|\n122: | Pros | High availability; prevents duplicate deletions |\n123: | Cons | Complexity; requires lease management; adds coordination overhead for S-size task |\n124: \n125: **Decision**: Deferred. Current single-instance GC suffices for initial implementation. Leader election can be added when HA deployment is required.\n126: \n127: ## Risks\n128: \n129: | Risk | Mitigation |\n130: |------|------------|\n131: | GC overload during peak sandbox count | Batch limit (GCBatchSize=16) throttles deletions per cycle |\n132: | Concurrent runOnce calls race condition | `runOnce` is only called from single goroutine; store uses mutex protection |\n133: | GC stuck on slow deletion | `onceTimeout` limits total GC cycle duration; individual deletions have `DeletionTimeout` |\n134: | MemoryStore query performance with large sandbox count | In-memory index; sorted by expiry/activity time; limit truncates results |\n135: | Missing LastActivity updates | Ensure activity tracking in sandbox creation/heartbeat handlers |\n136: | GC stops unexpectedly | `Stop()` waits for goroutine completion via `sync.WaitGroup` |\n137: \n138: ## Implementation Notes\n139: \n140: 1. **Constants**: `GCBatchSize = 16`, `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 * time.Minute`\n141: 2. **Deletion Flow**: GC calls `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox` which handles both K8s CR deletion and store cleanup\n142: 3. **Reason Tracking**: `determineDeletionReason` categorizes deletions as `IdleTimeout`, `MaxDurationReached`, or `UserRequest`\n143: 4. **Error Handling**: NotFound errors are ignored (already deleted); other errors logged but don't stop GC cycle\n144: 5. **Configurable Idle Timeout**: `SetIdleTimeout` allows runtime adjustment via HTTP API (future)\n145: 6. **Test Coverage**: Unit tests verify expired/inactive cleanup, batch limits, concurrent safety\n146: \n147: ## References\n148: \n149: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Implementation\n150: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - Test coverage\n151: - `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - DeleteSandbox delegation\n152: - `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` - ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes\n153: - `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Default timeout constants\n154: - Kubernetes TTL Controller: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/\n\n(End of file - total 154 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a time-based garbage collection mechanism for Sandbox resources in the Workload Manager. This ensures automatic cleanup of expired and idle sandboxes, preventing resource accumulation and cluster bloat. The GC mechanism provides:\n\n1. **TTL Enforcement**: Automatically deletes sandboxes that exceed their `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n2. **Idle Timeout Cleanup**: Removes sandboxes with no activity beyond the configured idle timeout\n3. **Batch Processing**: Limits cleanup operations per cycle to avoid overwhelming the cluster\n4. **Configurable Intervals**: Adjustable GC cycle and idle timeout durations\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector struct with Start/Stop lifecycle, runLoop, runOnce methods |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior (expired, inactive, batch limits, concurrency) |\n| `Store interface extensions` | `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` and `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` methods |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775903862686,"end":1775903862696}}}}
